summary: An ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to purchase Five Thousand ($5,000) Dollars King County General Obligation 5's dated Feb. 1, 1908 and due Feb. 1, 1928 at One hundred one and fourteen hundredths ($101.14) Dollars, and accrued interest, and appropriating Five thousand one hundred ($5,100.00) Dollars, or as much thereof as may be necessary from the Water Bonds Sinking Fund.
